VIRGINIA, 536 U.S. 304 (2002) as to (01)  Naeem J. Williams  re  2064 ,  2243   -  Signed by JUDGE J. MICHAEL SEABRIGHT on 3/6/2014.  "For the foregoing reasons, Defendant has failed to prove that he  is intellectually  disabled for purposes of the Federal Death Penalty Act and  Atkins v. Virginia, 536 U.S. 304 (2002). He remains eligible to face the  death penalty. Defendant's Motion for such a pretrial determination is DENIED. This denial, however, doe s not preclude Defendant from raising these issues at  a punishment phase of the trial as part of an attempt to demonstrate mitigating  factors, should he be found guilty of one of the capital counts of the  Indictment."
